Political thugs invaded the All Progressives Congress (APC) State Secretariat in Abeokuta, Ogun State, in the early hours of Friday and took away important documents.
A chieftain of the party, Derin Adebiyi, was said to have remarked that nobody has been arrested in connection with the incident, adding that the invasion has been reported to the security agencies for investigation. He noted that the thugs overwhelmed every staff at the state secretariat and invaded the office of the state chairman, including the state secretary and the state organizing secretary.
ALSO READ: Imo Deputy Speaker resigns
“The attack was massive. All offices were broken into, including the office of the chairman, the state secretary, the organising secretary, among others.
“All offices were ransacked and important documents were taken away. Properties were vandalised,” he narrated.
Adebiyi could not clarify on the extent of damage caused by the invaders, he, however, stated that the intention of the attackers is still unknown but suspicious.

			
